	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post144944"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"Cami?" Talvarien asked after Camille finished her story.<br />
<br />
"Hmm?" she replied.<br />
<br />
"Are you going to preface every meal by making me sick to my stomach?" he asked. "That has to be the most disturbing thing I've heard since I compared my armor class to a pure caster's." Then after a pause, "Scratch that, I forgot about the manginas."<br />
<br />
Grelin was lost in thought, having sunk to his haunches when Camille began Katarin's recount and not having moved since. Roc was contemplating what she had told him, from start to finish, stroking his chin thoughtfully.<br />
<br />
"Well," Roc said after a moment. "That explains why Promethian cancelled its raids. So what have we got here, when you bring all of this together?" He started ticking down facts on his fingers. "One, Promethian Order hits Terris, and finds a statue of River there. One they think was stolen from River's memorial, but it isn't; no statue was ever made, that you know of." Camille nodded.<br />
<br />
"Two," he continued. "Akethadar, being Akethadar, has the statue brought back to his guildhouse, and begins using it as a punching bag. I knew Ake's capabilities as a monk, he was top class. That thing should have been reduced to gravel. But it didn't break. The statue's creator, whomever it was, used something beyond normal rock to form it. Ake flipping out on the statue is a little wacky, but nothing unusual, given Akethadar and Riverdane's crappy past."<br />
<br />
"No love, all hate." Talvarien chimed in.<br />
<br />
"Three." Roc said, and then again with that whooping cough. They waited. "Three. Promethian Order invades Grieg's End, the old castle of Grieg the Geomancer. Greig should be dead long ago and it should just be them getting past those crazy traps and looting the place, but Grieg is ALIVE somehow, and gets alone with Akethadar before they actually kill him. They clean the place out, except for some blue gem, and leave.<br />
<br />
"Four, I'm running out of fingers here. Four. Ake loses his mind completely, even by Ake standards, and has Tremas port the statue to Luclin, and, I may add, the Dawnshroud port, close to Grieg's castle. These funky guys in black scarves drag away the statue. Tremas's magic doesn't work, and they have to run away to actually get off the moon. Akethadar finally loses it completely, and raiding in Promethian grinds to a halt."<br />
<br />
"Dreams..." Grelin adds suddenly from his spot near the ground.<br />
<br />
"Ah, yes," Roc says, tapping his thumb. "Five, all of this oddly correlates to Camille's recent nightmares. The statue of River, the actual battle against Terris by Promethian, the whole 'Free' thing. I bet a sack of plat that Camille's details of that fight match exactly, down the dead druid and switching of opening tactics. And I'll bet that evil voice, the 'free' voice, was Grieg. But the rest? River's 'Avenge' and whatnot? And those glowing rocks the scarved guys were burying on the moon? No idea. Maybe River speaking was just Camille's head talking for River, I don't know. And that business on the moon is beyond me. And why exactly Camille is picking up these images I'm clueless. We live in odd times, Cami. The dead do indeed walk, just take a look at Befallen and the Estate of Unrest. Perhaps you are the victim of a haunting. River was stubborn enough in life, I'd expect him worse in death." Camille just frowned, taking that in.<br />
<br />
"And now," Roc said, standing up and stretching out. "I'd like to eat. I'm hungry as hells."<br />
<br />
"Well, YOU can toss the salad." Talvarien said. "Once she got to the 'Akethadar gouged his eyes out' part, only thing I want to toss is my breakfast."<br />
<br />
"I got it." Grelin said, standing up and moving to the salad.<br />
<br />
"I'm with Talv," Camille remarked. "I've lost my appetite for the night. I think I'm going to head to bed early and think about all this."<br />
<br />
"Night Cami." Talvarien waved, starting to kindle a fire at the fireplace.<br />
<br />
"Night, girl." Rocsalt said, moving over to the larder and taking out some bread. "Where the hells do you people keep the butter?"<br />
<br />
"Night." Grelin called over his shoulder, generously adding two more tomatoes to the salad.<br />
<br />
"Night." Camille said absently, and disappeared in the direction of her room.</font></p>
	
