<!-- spacer --></td><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td></tr></table>
<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post145095"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >She waked as if cold water had been thrown on her, the sound of her scream continuing on faintly in the night, hands twisting the bedsheet into a torn clump. After a breathless pause, she realized it wasn't the echo of her scream she heard; that was only in the dream. Thankfully for the rest of the house, it had never reached her lips. But there was a high pitched noise coming from outside.<br />
<br />
Still in her white nightdress, she climbed out of her bed and went to the window. Still night, and dark. She was wide awake, the nightmare having dissipated any fog of sleep that may have still clung to her. Luclin was nothing more than a crescent, as she looked out the window towards the source of the shrill wail. The stables. Brimstone was awake and agitated inside.<br />
<br />
Without bothering to get a robe, she made her way barefoot down the halls and outside. Normally she would have approached the horse in full armor, considering the hellion he had become. But the whinnies seemed urgent, frightened, and to lose time while dressing for battle would have taken too long. She did, however, grab River's sword, Reaver, from the wall. The steel glinted slightly in the little moonlight the quarter moon afforded as she made her way across the grass to the stable.<br />
<br />
Unlocking the stable doors quickly, she entered the stables, Reaver gripped in one hand tightly. Brimstone neighed loudly as she slipped inside, but did not do its custom lunge at her, to her relief. Instead it just danced back.<br />
<br />
"What's wrong?" she asked the horse, half expecting it to answer. No answer except it dancing nervously. She reached out a hand tentatively towards the trembling horse, ready to pull back if it tried to bite like it usually did. But not tonight. Closer she drew.<br />
<br />
Contact, finally, after a year. She touched her hand to Brimstone's mane.<br />
<br />
Hot. She had forgotten after a year how unnaturally warm the horse's bodyheat was. She ran her hand through its mane as its prancing slowed and stopped. It snorted once and was still under her caress.<br />
<br />
"What, you crazy horse?" she repeated, brushing her hand through its mane. It moved closer to her, lowering its head under her moving fingers. Slowly it nuzzled against her arm. After all that time fighting the horse, she felt like crying. It was finally accepting her.<br />
<br />
She found herself swinging up onto its back before she registered she was doing it. No saddle, reins, anything, just climbed up on a stool, sword still in hand, and onto the stallion's back. She ran her hand again through its mane, surprised she had made that bold a move, but everything seemed controlled.<br />
<br />
"Now, you want to canter out and...." she began.<br />
<br />
Then, clearly, in her mind, she clearly heard the thoughts of the horse, as if it had spoken out loud in common.<br />
<br />
--NOW, HUMAN. LET'S SEE IF YOU CAN RIDE.--<br />
<br />
And with a snort of fire from its nostrils, Brimstone bolted out of the stable, Camille still in her nightgown, one hand grasping Reaver, the other in a deathgrip on the horse's mane, as they charged into the dark night.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><a href="report.php?s=3288aedf0a1cf8f86d293cf642ed2fa4&postid=145095">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=3288aedf0a1cf8f86d293cf642ed2fa4&action=getip&postid=145095">Logged</a></font></p>
