<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post145427"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Camille's eyes, even before they pierced the gloom, knew where she was.<br />
<br />
The lair of Terris Thule.<br />
<br />
Terris still lay on the ground where Camille had seen her last, dress shredded around her, soaked in caked blood. Most of the puddles of blood had reduced themselves to dry dark stains on the floor. Terris' wounds were all gone, without a scar, but she did not move.<br />
<br />
~~dismount~~ came that disembodied voice, but now with some direction. It was coming from Terris herself.<br />
<br />
Camille, for the first time since the insane journey had begun, loosened her leg muscles and released her grip on Brimstone's mane. She half slid, half fell off the horse, exhausted, every sinew screaming. She landed uneasily on her feet, and then just slid abruptly to the ground, panting. She feared she would never walk again.<br />
<br />
Slowly, painstakingly, Terris rolled over, without a sound of rustled cloth, to lay on her side and yet look upon Camille. The goddess' breast heaved as her nostrils flared out and in, taking in air. Her huge dark eyes scrutinized the sprawled out paladin, dressed only in her sleeping gown, still clutching her husband's sword.<br />
<br />
For a long time they just contemplated each other silently.<br />
<br />
~~you are a strong woman, to have survived that~~<br />
<br />
"So are you," Camille remarked, looking at the dark stains on the ground.<br />
<br />
~~i am a goddess, i will never truly die, until the day mortals finally succeed in their little dream of conquest, and kill us all in the plane of time ~ then they can see how they like a world with no gods ~ akethadar and his dogs did not kill me, just my avatar, and slowly, over time i will be whole again ~ and then i suppose they will be back, as mortals always are ~ although i imagine akethadar will not be leading the next set, no no~~ and the sound of a chuckle that chilled Camille.<br />
<br />
"Did you drive Akethadar mad?" Camille asked bluntly.<br />
<br />
~~me?~~ Terris asked, actually surprised, ~~i wouldn't touch that man's mind even if the nameless commanded me to ~ no, camille wyldechylde, the only mind i have touched in quite a while has been yours~~<br />
<br />
"The dreams. You sent them to me."<br />
<br />
~~yes ~ garbled at first as i was weak, very weak ~ later stronger ones, and finally, the will to have the horse bring you here~~<br />
<br />
"If you didn't read Akethadar's mind, why the statue of River?" Camille asked, so many questions bouncing around in her mind. "How would you know?"<br />
<br />
~~ah, the statue~~ Terris said, ~~it was here for the last year ~ where did you think your husband's soul went, to innoruuk? ~ in the end he chose me to worship~~<br />
<br />
"I see." Camille said shortly, hurt in some undescribable way, unable to stop a pang of jealousy from striking her heart. Terris picked up on it.<br />
<br />
~~ah, you mistake the term worship, mithaniel's handmaiden ~ when faced with which plane his soul would reside in, he chose me, for whatever effect our business with end game had had on him ~ but, from the state of his dreams when he was here, he dreamed of you ~ only you~~<br />
<br />
Camille didn't know whether Terris had said that to appease her or was speaking the truth, but the words acted as a salve for her pained heart. But still her question was unanswered.<br />
<br />
"So you erected a statue of him here?" Camille asked, confused.<br />
<br />
~~no~~ Terris replied, ~~that was no statue of any rock known to man ~ that was a soulcasing, my own creation ~ you saw my gargoyles, they are of the same stone~~<br />
<br />
"Soulcasing." Camille said blankly.<br />
<br />
~~yes, my other four worshipers, yes, only four, were all demons, and thus their likenesses as grotesque ~ the soulcasing can hold the living soul that exists after the body dies~~<br />
<br />
"So when River died," Camille said, hope lighting her face as stared at Terris. "He did not die?"<br />
<br />
~~yes, and no~~ Terris said. ~~the soul if preserved will never truly die, so while his time among mortals was done, he lived on dreaming in the soulcasing i provided for him ~ in times of dire stress, i wake the dreamers to protect me, but river ~~~ would not ~ you saw that~<br />
<br />
"I saw." Camille replied, recalling the dream.<br />
<br />
~~he suspected that i would eventually survive the attack, while promethian would not ~ even against his sworn enemy he would not attack with the strength the soulcasing would have lended him~~<br />
<br />
"River didn't hate Akethadar." Camille said.<br />
<br />
~~but akethadar hated him ~ oh how he hated him ~ and grieg saw that, saw the statue in akethadar's mind, even as he died, and jumped on it~~<br />
<br />
"Grieg." Camille said, seizing upon the name to change subjects to more of her questions. "Where does he fit into this?"<br />
<br />
~~grieg veneficus was a brilliant geomancer, the top of his class ~ long ago his studies with the magic inherant in stone and earth allowed for travel to luclin, where he brought the combine ~ when he failed to discover a route back in timely fashion, however, he was spurned, and forced into his castle to discover a route back ~ but luclin the deity was enjoying the new additions to her little world, and drove grieg mad in his home, and set up clever mind-altering guardians to guard both him ever leaving his castle and anyone entering ~ the insanity also had the unusual side effect of keeping him alive long after he should have died, as his body rotted and changed into a blobbish purple mass ~ grieg festered like an open wound in his home while others finally found a way to open a two way portal to the moon, and was forgotten ~ but he never forgot the outside world, or the wrongs they had suffered upon him~~<br />
<br />
Slowly Terris propped herself up into a sitting position, and continued.<br />
<br />
~~over the years of his imprisonment, grieg had still worked on his experiments, but now for his own dark purpose ~ one of these was the creation of a blue gem that he called the geomancer's stone ~ the gem was part prison, part battery~~<br />
<br />
"I don't understand." Camille cut in.<br />
<br />
~~patience, mithaniel's handmaiden~~ Terris shhed her, then went on as Camille fell silent, more questions dying on her lips. ~~the geomancer's stone could act as a housing for a soul without a soulcasing, to preserve the soul, very similiar to what the statue of riverdane could do ~ and once a soul was inside it, could be used as a power source for mechanical devices, drawing on the lifeforce of the soul within, consuming it as it magnified that lifeforce to energy many many times the size of the actual soul ~ eventually, the soul would be snuffed out, but the power output would be astronomical~~<br />
<br />
"My dreams." Camille said, face pale, "River....is in that gem."<br />
<br />
~~yes~~ Terris confirmed. ~~when akethadar killed grieg, grieg tapped his mind and saw the statue, and knowing more about stone than any other living man, knew the soulcasing for what it was ~ he planted the seed of insanity into akethadar's brain, like a parasite, and then escaped with his own soul into the geomancer's stone, and waited ~ waited for akethadar's mind to be eaten away, and to answer the hypnotic order greig had placed in him ~ to deliver the statue to the moon ~ grieg's servants, local natives whom grieg's magic had bound and twisted, recovered the statue and brought it to the geomancer's stone, where grieg, powered with insanity and taking riverdane quite by surprise, forced riverdane's soul out of the soulcasing and took his place ~ river, having no other place to go, slipped into the geomancer's stone~<br />
<br />
"River..." Camille said helplessly.<br />
<br />
~~is trapped~~ Terris continued. ~~now grieg has a form that can move and is nearly indestructable in one on one combat ~ and riverdane is trapped in the geomancer's stone, unable to leave, with nowhere to go ~ and freedom is not the only thing grieg wanted ~ he is currently working on another experiment, and i suspect he intends to use river's soul to power it ~ grieg's mind is too twisted to read, and he does not dream, not for even a second ~ the insanity luclin placed on him ate any capacity he had for dreams ~ so i do not know what the madman is planning to do, only that river's soul is in great peril, and knowing grieg's insanity, so are a great many more~~<br />
<br />
"River was trying to tell me something. YOU were trying to tell me something!" Camille exclaimed, panic in her tone. "What does 'Avenge' have to do with this? Avenge River? You?"<br />
<br />
Terris stared blankly at her. ~~avenge?~~<br />
<br />
"Yes!" Camille said with frustration. "In the dream, River said 'Avenge', 'Venge'; you, YOU said 'Venge'!" But Terris just continued to stare at her with no comprehension in her eyes. Then suddenly, Terris' eyes narrowed a moment.<br />
<br />
~~ahh, no, not avenge~~ Terris said. ~~it never fails to amaze me how you mortals hear things and don't hear, twisting things to suit what you think they mean ~ the word i wanted you to hear was vven~~<br />
<br />
"Ven?" Camille asked, confused.<br />
<br />
~~two v's~~ Terris sighed.<br />
<br />
Camille's mouth dropped open, as she began to understand. "Vven? The enchanter that helped River during End Game?"<br />
<br />
~~yes~~<br />
<br />
"How does Vven figure into this at all?" Camille asked, confused again.<br />
<br />
~~when your husband and his companions were here, i opened up his mind, to read his past and his intentions ~ his friends suspected i was also picking through their minds ~ and they were right ~ i remember a fragment from vven of a meeting at some point in his life with grieg, a flash in time, but i remember it ~ enough so for me to believe that vven psyphon may have more information on grieg's intent, even though the teir'dal may not realize it himself ~ seek him, and find answers~~<br />
<br />
"Thank you, Terris." Camille said softly, reaching out to place her palm over the goddess' massive hand. Terris allowed it, an odd look in her eyes at the woman's touch of sisterhood. "Why? Why did you tell me all this?"<br />
<br />
~~you love him~~ Terris said after a pause. ~~a year ago, riverdane wyldechylde helped return my love to me~i am repaying that favor~~ A pause and then, ~~and he was the only mortal other than demons to choose me~~<br />
<br />
Camille nodded, understanding. Then her eyes suddenly brimmed with tears. "And the dreams, River talking to me, holding me....was that really him or...?"<br />
<br />
~~that was me~~ Terris said sadly. ~~trace memories from him lending me script for the dream ~ i am sorry i made you think he was speaking to you~~<br />
<br />
Camille wiped her eyes as that sunk in. Knights don't cry. "Thank you all the same. Even in a nightmare, it helped keep him alive for me."<br />
<br />
~~mount the horse, mithaniel's handmaiden~~ Terris said gently. ~~i promise you safe passage back to your home~~ She laboriously drew herself from her feet, and lifted Camille up like a doll to place her on the back of Brimstone, still clutching River's sword. Then Terris passed her hand in front of Camille's eyes.<br />
<br />
~~sleep~~ Terris intoned, and Camille collapsed weakly against Brimstone's neck, deep in slumber. Terris sent her magic out into the woman to keep her from sliding off.<br />
<br />
~~sleep, camille wyldechylde, and for your lost nights in my nightmares, dream of what you wish~~ Terris commanded the paladin in her nightdress, sword hanging from one limp hand. <br />
<br />
~~bring her safely back to the stables, brimstone~~ Terris said quietly.<br />
<br />
--YES, MISTRESS.-- the horse whinnied, unable to disobey. Terris slumped weakly to her knees, the whole conversation having drained more out of her than she would have preferred.<br />
<br />
~~and fetch rallos to me~~</font></p>
	
