<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post146260"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Camille awoke suddenly, body stiff. She blinked twice in surprise, not quite sure where she was. Pale light lit the stable, as she realized she was laying on a pile of hay. My gods, she thought, I slept till dawn. The memory of the dream was quickly escaping her the way dreams do, and she felt a pang of loss as the recollection of her first meeting River slowly faded away. It wasn't without its bad parts, the dream, but when his lips had touched her hand...<br />
<br />
She suddenly realized she was not alone in the stable. Grelin sat on his haunches, a silly grin on his face, watching her. When her eyes met his, he smiled wider, stood, and ran out of the stables. She rose, groaning to her feet. Brimstone was no where to be seen. Reaver was still gripped in her hand. With horror she noticed that it was covered in blood, as was the hay where it had laid.<br />
<br />
Grelin returned, with Rocsalt in tow. And slowing, limping severely, Talvarien entered the stable behind them, eyeing Camille warily and giving her a large berth.<br />
<br />
"I'm sorry if I worried you, guys." Camille began, stepping forward. Talvarien scuttled backwards, terror in his eyes.<br />
<br />
"Cami," he said, panic in his voice. "Put DOWN the sword!Down girl! Don't hurt the Talv...."<br />
<br />
"Huh?" she asked, confusion in her eyes.<br />
<br />
"Before Talvarien has an accident in his pants, I suggest you put down the sword, Cami." Roc suggested. "He's already had enough for one day."<br />
<br />
"I don't understand," Camille said.<br />
<br />
"You stabbed him." Grelin grinned.<br />
<br />
"I WHAT?" Camille said in shock, stepping towards Talvarien.<br />
<br />
"DON'T HURT ME!" Talv half-shrieked, pulling Rocsalt in front of him.<br />
<br />
"Talv!" Camille said, slowly placing the bloody sword onto the ground. "I'm sorry...I....what happened??" She took two steps deliberately away from the sword.<br />
<br />
"When we woke up and you missed breakfast, we started looking for you." Roc said. "Talv tracked you to the stable, found you sleeping in the hay. He tried to wake you up."<br />
<br />
"And you tried to KILL me like a crazy woman!" Talv wailed. "Where's the love? None!"<br />
<br />
"You sliced him in the leg, without even opening your eyes. And then you went right on sleeping." Rocsalt said, with a half smile. "He screamed like a little girl."<br />
<br />
"It HURT!" Talv exclaimed indignantly. "It took three ranja heals to stop me from bleeding to death."<br />
<br />
"Bah." Roc said. "It takes a full ranger heal to heal a mosquito bite. You were fine after Grelin popped a regen on you. And what's with the limp?"<br />
<br />
"I'll be a gimp for life." Talvarien predicted.<br />
<br />
"You're gimp now." Grelin replied.<br />
<br />
"No love!" Talvarien exclaimed, and was silent.<br />
<br />
"Talv, I'm sorry, I didn't know what I was doing." Camille apologized sincerely. "I've had a....long night. And long day it seems. I missed breakfast? That means..."<br />
<br />
"Aye," Roc finished for her. "It's sunset now. You slept the whole day away."<br />
<br />
"The whole day." Camille said, agitated. River was locked in that gem, and she was sleeping away what could be precious time. "Let's get back to the guildhouse, guys. I need to get into some clothes and tell you what happened."<br />
<br />
She picked up Reaver, and left towards the house, Rocsalt and Grelin at her side. Talvarien fell into step behind them, with a careful eye on Camille's swordhand, but the limp miraculously gone. He was as curious as the other two to where Brimstone had gone and why Camille was asleep in the stables.<br />
<br />
Grelin fixed a quick dinner as Camille detailed her meeting with Terris, the history of Grieg, the use of the blue gem, every little detail she could remember. They ate quietly while she told the tale, stopping every now and then to eat. She was ravenous. At the end she sat back, exhausted by the retelling.<br />
<br />
"So what do we do now, head over to Greig's place and bust River out, powpowpowpow?" Talvarien said, all thoughts of his little injury forgotten.<br />
<br />
"No." Grelin said, shaking his head.<br />
<br />
"You remember what Katarin said about that statue." Rocsalt added. "Akethadar couldn't scratch it. It would be suicide to head in there just us four."<br />
<br />
"Plus Terris wanted me to talk to Vven first." Camille said, recalling how insistant the goddess had been. "He may have some answers for us that will make some sense."<br />
<br />
"I haven't seen Vven Psyphon since.....since my arms got ripped off and they buried me during End Game." Talvarien said with a shudder.<br />
<br />
"He stayed on in Hate, taking my place when Innoruuk demanded a soul be paid." Camille said, remembering back two years ago. "I bet he is still there."<br />
<br />
"Then we need to get to Hate." Roc said, standing up. "Which means..."<br />
<br />
"We need a wizard." Camille finished.</font></p>
	
