<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post146633"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"Verdad, let us in!" Camille called again, knocking on the door urgently.<br />
<br />
"Not home?" Grelin suggested.<br />
<br />
"He's home, I see candlelight in the windows." Camille said, knocking again. "My mother was a wizard, she would never leave a lit fire in the house if her and my father were out. Wizards respect the power of fire too much."<br />
<br />
"Allow me." Rocsalt said, stepping forward. He rapped his knuckles on the door, hard.<br />
<br />
Inside, the sound of a door opening hastily, and then the locks clicking open. The door swung open.<br />
<br />
"Come in, A...." Verdad began, standing in the doorway in nothing but black boxers decorated in bright red hearts. A half finished bottle of wine was in one hand. As he took in the four in his doorway, his mouth dropped open in surprise.<br />
<br />
"Sorry to call this late, Verd." Camille apologized, "But I need a favor."<br />
<br />
"Um, bad time guys...." Verdad began, finding his voice, turning his head to a closed door behind him nervously. The sound of falling water stopped, and Verdad looked back at them imploringly.<br />
<br />
"Nice duds. Is that real silk?" Talvarien said, slipping past Verdad into the room. Verdad turned with him, panic in his eyes, as the rest filed into the room. "Wowowow, look at this place!" Talvarien exclaimed, taking in the lush couch, with the candelabras lit in all corners, half eaten cheese platter on the marble table, plush tigerskin rug. Outer clothing was scattered all over the couch, some male, some female. "Is this an original?" he asked, pointing to a satyr and nymph orgy scene framed on the wall.<br />
<br />
Verdad quickly closed the door behind them as they invaded his living room. "Cami, heh, I would never close my door to you, I hope you know that, but your timing is a little...."<br />
<br />
"Verd, I wouldn't have come if it weren't important." Camille said honestly. But Verdad was only half listening, still looking at the door from which the sound of water had stopped.<br />
<br />
"Any other time, ok?" Verdad begged.<br />
<br />
"Good cheese!" Talvarien said, popping another piece in his mouth.<br />
<br />
"I need to get to Hate." Camille said quickly.<br />
<br />
"Hate?" Verdad blinked. "Just get on that horse of River's. You still have it, don't you?"<br />
<br />
Suddenly the door swung open, and a redheaded highelf, dressed only a towel, walked out, facedown as she wrapped up her hair in another towel, water dripping onto the carpet.<br />
<br />
"So where is this surprise you promi..." she began, looking up. And then her mouth dropped open as she took in the room.<br />
<br />
"Jazzy..." Verdad began, hands up in supplication as her face grew dark.<br />
<br />
"THIS is the surprise?" she exclaimed indignantly, anger rising. "FOUR PEOPLE??"<br />
<br />
"We lost the horse." Talvarien answered for Camille obliviously, popping another piece of cheese into his mouth.<br />
<br />
"HORSE??" Jazzy shrieked.<br />
<br />
"Jazzy it's not what it seems..." Verdad began, face crumbling.<br />
<br />
But she was not listening. She stalked over to the couch and grabbed up her robes. "You sick perverted..." and a string of colorful curses as she stormed into the bathroom and slammed the door behind her.<br />
<br />
"Sorry, Verdad." Camille said, mortified. <br />
<br />
"You're cramping my style!" Verdad wailed, and then a knock on the door. Verdad's eyes went wild. "Don't get..."<br />
<br />
"I got it." Talv said blithely, swinging open the door.<br />
<br />
In the doorway, another, younger high elven girl stood with her eyes closed, wearing a long black trenchcoat. The moment the door swung open, she opened the trenchcoat wide with a smile. Underneath she was wearing two tassels, a skimpy loin cloth and.....nothing else.<br />
<br />
"I wore it!" she said brightly, eyes still closed. "Where's my surprise??"<br />
<br />
"Surprise." Grelin said, grinning.<br />
<br />
The girl's eyes snapped open.<br />
<br />
"Aiene...." Verdad began.<br />
<br />
"Impressive." Rocsalt commented, eyebrows raised, as Aiene hastily covered herself with the trenchcoat.<br />
<br />
"There's no horse!" Talvarien added emphatically.<br />
<br />
Aiene screamed.<br />
<br />
"Aiene..." Verdad tried again, when Jazzy swung open the bathroom door, now fully dressed, and took in the latest addition in shock.<br />
<br />
"Oh my gods, you sick bastard!" Jazzy exclaimed. "Aiene too? She's only seventeen!"<br />
<br />
"Today's my birthday." Aiene said miserably.<br />
<br />
"She's legal now!" Verdad tried desperately.<br />
<br />
"And there's NO horse! None!" Talvarien piped up helpfully.<br />
<br />
"Perverts!" Jazzy exclaimed, shooting Verdad a murderous look. He took a tentative step toward her, but her eyes narrowed and she disappeared from view, gating.<br />
<br />
"Aiene..." Verdad sighed, turning back to the girl in his doorway. She was fuming.<br />
<br />
"YOU RUINED MY BIRTHDAY!" she screamed, eyes lighting gold. A white hammer materialized in the air, hovering for a moment.<br />
<br />
"Not in the face!" Verdad cried, as the hammer flew at him. He ducked.<br />
<br />
--SMASH-- the hammer hit Talvarien full in the face, breaking his nose.<br />
<br />
"Ranja...down..." Talvarien said weakly, slumping onto the couch.<br />
<br />
"Aiene..." Verdad tried again, but the girl blinked, and like Jazzy, gated.<br />
<br />
"Verdad..." Camille began lamely.<br />
<br />
"You're KILLING me here, Cami!" Verdad growled, looking distraught in his boxers.<br />
<br />
"Verd, I wouldn't have come if this wasn't important!" Camille pleaded. "It's about River..."<br />
<br />
"River is dead, Cami," Verdad said, miffed. "As I have been trying to remind you for the last six months..." He suddenly tapered off, a nervous look crossing his face. "Um, he IS dead, right?"<br />
<br />
"Yes and no..." Camille began.<br />
<br />
"Ah dammit, Grelin, fix Talv's nose!" Verdad exclaimed, noticing the ranjer groaning behind him. "He's bleeding all over the damned couch..."<br />
<br />
"Easy with the schnozz!" Talvarien yelped, as Grelin touched his fingers, glowing green, to Talvarien's shattered nose.<br />
<br />
"So what exactly did you wreck my life for?" Verdad asked, shrugging into a robe and sinking into an easy chair.<br />
<br />
And Camille, for the second time that night, told her tale.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
