	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post146869"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"This is unreal." Verdad commented, staring at Camille when she finished.<br />
<br />
"It's real alright, Verd." Camille replied.<br />
<br />
"You know," Verdad said, "It's getting to the point where I'm afraid when I see a Wyldechylde."<br />
<br />
"Will you help?" Camille asked, looking him in the eye.<br />
<br />
"On one condition." Verdad said.<br />
<br />
"And that is?"<br />
<br />
"Dinner when this is over." Verdad said, watching her.<br />
<br />
"Not a chance."<br />
<br />
"Ok, I'll do it anyway." Verdad sighed.<br />
<br />
"Thank you, Verd." Camille smiled. "We need to leave at once."<br />
<br />
"Ok, stone please." Verdad said, standing up.<br />
<br />
"Stone?" Camille said blankly.<br />
<br />
Verdad sighed. "Hate stone. I need a reagent to port."<br />
<br />
Camille looked flustered, and glanced around at the lost looks of her companions. "I...err..don't...."<br />
<br />
"You didn't bring a rock." Verdad finished for her. "Ok, buckle up, we're headed to the Nektulos. I need to see a guy River turned me on to that can work the inside."<br />
<br />
"Nektulos?" Camille asked, confused.<br />
<br />
"The only place port stone to Hate are sold are in Neriak. There's a guy I use in there for potions and other oddities." And then, with a word in elvish, they shimmered and disappeared.<br />
<br />
With a flash of light, they found themselves on the flat-topped pyramid that was the wizard portal in the Nektulos Forest, which housed the teir'dal city of Neriak. Verdad started off, motioning for them to stay.<br />
<br />
"I'll be back in about ten minutes." he said over his shoulder.<br />
<br />
Talvarien glanced down at the ground and then looked up. "Verd waitwaitwait."<br />
<br />
"What?" Verdad asked, stopping impatiently.<br />
<br />
"I'm picking up...." Talvarien began, running down the side of the pyramid and staring at the grass. "One two three...ten...twenty? More. Over twenty guards in full armor near here, and not long ago either."<br />
<br />
"Over twenty guards?" Verdad said incredulously. Not that he didn't believe him. They may be correct in doubting Talvarien could tie his boots without hurting himself, but when it came to tracking, they trusted the ranger's talents implicitly. It was just that large a force in the Nektulos was unheard of for a very long time.<br />
<br />
"Aye." Talv said, looking up, "And they're patrolling. They'll be back."<br />
<br />
"Well, I can send you all back to my place...." Verdad began.<br />
<br />
"We'll go with you." Camille suggested. "Grelin, Spirit of Eagle and Foilage Sheild please."<br />
<br />
Grelin nodded and began chanting. His first spell lifted them up in the air, levitating them, lending speed to their movement, and blessed their eyes to see the invisible. The second spell made them disappear from normal sight, though they all saw each other plainly.<br />
<br />
"Alright, while it holds." Verdad said, "Let's move."<br />
<br />
They made their way double quick through the forest to the city of Neriak.</font></p>
	
