<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post147153"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Verdad turned to them outside the filthy hut deep in Neriak's Foreign Quarter, and mouthed, This is it. Camille nodded, and followed Verdad into the rundown shack, the others on her heels.<br />
<br />
She stopped dead as a dog began to growl.<br />
<br />
And then a loud whipcrack as something in the shadows passed wind.<br />
<br />
"Shhhh, Stinky!" a decrepid voice called out from the gloom across the room. "Don't growl at the dinner guests! Kekkekekkekkekekke!"<br />
<br />
The dog's growl tapered off to a low snarl, but didn't stop.<br />
<br />
"Soso?" the voice asked, "Who be here? Sound off, cause I can't see you yet!"<br />
<br />
Verdad murmured something, and his hand began to glow with wizardfire, just enough to light the room for Camille and Rocsalt, his two human companions, with their weaker eyes.<br />
<br />
Across from them, sitting in the darkness stirring a large soup pot, was a disgusting troll. A filthy cur of a dog lay at his feet, hackles raised, looking at them dangerously.<br />
<br />
"We see you now, Scurg." Verdad said, addressing the troll.<br />
<br />
"Ah you see me, but I don't see you, see? Kekekekkekk! Soup needed radishes!" the troll laughed oddly, pointing up to his face. Both eyes were missing, leaving nothing but dark black holes in his face.<br />
<br />
"I'm so going to be sick." Talvarien moaned.<br />
<br />
"If you do, do it in the pot!" Scurg suggested. "So, I hear two. One voice I know, one I don't. But there are more yes? I hear your in out of breath! So who be you?"<br />
<br />
"Camille Wyldechylde." Camille offered, trying not to breathe in the stench.<br />
<br />
"Talvarien." Talv said, shifting uncomfortably.<br />
<br />
"Rocsalt. Di'Varr." Roc added, and able to finally make noise after their hushed trip through the city's outskirts, let go with his cough he had been surpressing.<br />
<br />
"Grelin." the druid finished.<br />
<br />
"Five! Old Scurg has five bless me, come to my home! Going to need more soup!" Then he turned roughly in Verdad's direction. "So, back so soon, paleface? Ran out of Scurg's Spirit of Rabbit already? Lady friends like it, yes? Thumpthumpthumpthump done!"<br />
<br />
"Err..." Verdad said, face turning red. "I don't need any more potions, Scurg, thanks, I need..."<br />
<br />
"Ah, I know what you need." Scurg murmured, stirring his pot. "Scurg know lots of things."<br />
<br />
"I know Scurg is out of his freakin' gourd." Talvarien whispered to Rocsalt.<br />
<br />
"Kekekkkkekekkk, ranger boy!" Scurg said loudly, turning his eyeless face directly to Talvarien. "I threw my eyes into the soup, but not my ears! You may be right, you may be right, but it better to listen to a crazy man than to hear nothing at all, yesyes?"<br />
<br />
"Um, yeah." Talvarien said, embarrassed he had been heard.<br />
<br />
Scurg continued to stir his pot. "Yesyes, Scurg hear many things. Scurg see many thing, with or without radishes! Scurg see snakes slither across the face of the moon! Scurg smell a change in the wind!" And to punctuate that, he farted loudly.<br />
<br />
"Scurg," Verdad said suddenly. "There is increased patrols in the Nektulos. You know anything about that?"<br />
<br />
"Ahh, the darkies are up in arms!" Scurg gibbered, nodding. All cities are increasing their watches! Something strange afoot, for lighties and darkies both! The books of passage are gone, poof, stolen!"<br />
<br />
"Books of passage?" Rocsalt asked. <br />
<br />
"Yes, sick one." Scurg said, turning in Rocsalt's direction. Roc gave another involuntary cough, almost on cue. Camille glanced at him nervously before looking back to the troll.<br />
<br />
"What books of passage?" Camille asked.<br />
<br />
"He means the portal books to Plane of Knowledge," Verdad said slowly. "Don't you, Scurg?"<br />
<br />
"Yesyes," Scurg said, nodding vigorously, "Young lion smart as he is virile! Kekkekekkkekekke!"<br />
<br />
"What the hells?" Verdad asked. "Those books are fused to the pedestals they sit upon, to prevent theft."<br />
<br />
"But when the rock become soup, easy enough to pluck out the chicken!" Scurg chortled.<br />
<br />
"Rock becomes soup?" Verdad asked, confused.<br />
<br />
"Whoever take the books, melted the rock!" Scurg informed him, stirring the pot happily.<br />
<br />
"Odd." Rocsalt commented.<br />
<br />
"Great." Verdad moaned, looking at Grelin. "Well, Grel, get ready for a ton of 'Hey dood, can you port to West Commons for 5 plat?'..." Grelin nodded sadly. "So, Scurg, I need a Hate rock."<br />
<br />
"Ah, going up to see my old friend, aye? Tell him for Scurg things too quiet around here without him! Kekekekkkekke!" Then Scurg reached down under his seat, looking for something. "Hate stone, Hate stone..." he murmured. "Ah, here it be!" And he withdrew something from under his chair and held it in Talvarien's general direction. It was a lumpy shape, brown, and had a foul odor. Talvarien took it from the troll and stared at it, holding it in his hand.<br />
<br />
"Um, Scurg." Verdad said, "That's not a Hate stone."<br />
<br />
"Hmm?" Scurg asked, snatching it back from Talvarien. He sniffed it once. "So it ain't! Bad dog!" he scolded, as the dog cringed. "Bad Stinky! I told you, not in the house!"<br />
<br />
"Gah!" Talvarien exclaimed in disgust, frantically wiping his hands on his leggings.<br />
<br />
"Ah well, flavor for soup!" Scurg said, tossing the dog turd into the pot with a wet splash. "Now where be it?" and he went rummaging under hs chair again. After a short time, he brought up a black stone, looking very much like coal.<br />
<br />
"Ah here it be, yes?" Scurg said, holding it out.<br />
<br />
"I'm not touching it!" Talvarien cried.<br />
<br />
"That's it, Scurg, thanks." Verdad said, taking the stone from the troll. "Put it on my tab."<br />
<br />
"That I will, that I will, kekekekekke." the troll chuckled. "So....stay for dinner?" he pointed to the pot.<br />
<br />
"I'll pass." Talvarien said weakly, still wiping his hands.<br />
<br />
"We have to go, Scurg." Camille said politely, "But thank you."<br />
<br />
"Ahh, another time, maybe!" Scurg suggested brightly. Then he stared in Camille's direction. "Give Scurg some time with Mithaniel's handmaiden, yesyes? I have secrets for her."<br />
<br />
"No." Grelin and Rocsalt said in unison.<br />
<br />
Camille blinked, hearing herself addressed by the strange troll in what she had thought to be a semi-private name for her.<br />
<br />
"Guys, I'll be fine." she said slowly.<br />
<br />
"Cami..." Rocsalt began.<br />
<br />
"Do you doubt my ability to fight, Roc? Or am I just River's wife to you?" she said warningly, looking at him with an eyebrow raised. Rocsalt's mouth snapped shut and he said nothing.<br />
<br />
"Leave us a moment, I'll be right out." she said.<br />
<br />
"Gladly." Talvarien said, slipping out the front door.<br />
<br />
"Be quick Cami." Verdad said, "We'll be between the huts outside. We shouldn't be seen by the guards in this area."<br />
<br />
And, with a last look of disapproval from Grelin and Rocsalt, the men made their way outside.<br />
<br />
"Come closer, dreamer." Scurg chortled, stirring the soup. Camille obliged him and came closer to the blind troll.<br />
<br />
Suddenly, like a snake, he dropped his ladle into the soup and grabbed her right hand in both of hers. His grip was clammy but firm. Her first reaction was to strike him, but she kept that in check, as his grip was not for pain, but to emphasize his next speech.<br />
<br />
"Remember this, girlie!" the troll whispered, his face up close a picture of madness. "When you want to talk to the dead, they got no ears left when the worms finish with them! So, you wanna talk to the dead, you gotta speak their language! They say dead men tell no tales, but dead women got plenty to say! Heed the troll shammie! Scurg knows many things! And the Dane still got plenty to say, for a man with no tongue! Kekekkkekkkekekekkekekeke!"<br />
<br />
Camille, body recoiling from his insane chatter, yanked her hand out of his grasp.<br />
<br />
"Thank you..." she managed, making her way out the door, trying to make sense of his gibberish.<br />
<br />
"Anytime, girlie!" Scurg called out after her, "And when it's all done, come for soup!"<br />
<br />
"Ready?" Verdad said, seeing Camille appear in the alley.<br />
<br />
"Aye." she said.<br />
<br />
"What did that crazy bastard say to you?" Talvarien asked.<br />
<br />
"Later." Camille said distractedly, rubbing her hand absently where the troll had touched her, trying to get the clammy feeling out of her system.<br />
<br />
"Be ready for anything." Verdad warned. "I hear Hate has changed a bit."<br />
<br />
"I love the place." Rocsalt said. "I spent so many raids there I could pull it blindfolded."<br />
<br />
"Not anymore." Verdad corrected him, starting to chant.<br />
<br />
"Huh?" Rocsalt began.<br />
<br />
But then, the incantation done, they winked out of sight, as the slums of Neriak disappeared from around them.</font></p>
	
