<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post147222"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Hate had....changed.<br />
<br />
They appeared around a shallow well, one Camille had never seen before in her previous raids on the home of Innoruuk. Normally you would arrive in Hate in a small abandoned building, praying that you wouldn't be swarmed by patrolling mobs that milled without direction through the streets. Now, you were outside on the streets in a corner, with no instant flurry of action, since the streets were deserted.<br />
<br />
"They removed the second floor." Rocsalt commented, glancing up. Camille followed his gaze. The low ceiling of the plane of Hate had disappeared, and the gothic buildings soared into the heights, arched and majestic, the architecture impressive in the pale blue glow that seemed to light the plane.<br />
<br />
"So, the reports were right." Verdad said. "Zone in is safe...."<br />
<br />
Talvarien was inspecting the walls surrounding the well with interest, reaching out to touch the bricks. "Wowowow, look at the stonework on this wa..." <br />
<br />
"Who dares invade the home of Innoruuk?" a spite golem growled from somewhere on the other side of the wall.<br />
<br />
"More victims for the Father!" cackled an unseen loathesome lich.<br />
<br />
"Blerg blerg!" cried an evil little imp.<br />
<br />
"Ooops?" Talvarien said lamely.<br />
<br />
"Same old aggro problems." Rocsalt sighed. He took a defensive posture as Camille drew Reaver out of its scabbard and prepared.<br />
<br />
From around the corner came a crowd of Hate's denizens.<br />
<br />
"So not good...." Talvarien said nervously, drawing his bow.<br />
<br />
"No chanters, I'm using areas..." Verdad murmured, hands glowing. Grelin looked around helplessly at the dead end they were trapped in.<br />
<br />
"Succor no good." he said.<br />
<br />
"No." Verdad agreed. "Probably drop us off right here again."<br />
<br />
Surrounded, the mob of liches, revenants, clerics, and other nightmares came towards them.<br />
<br />
"Cami! Verd!" came a loud happy voice from the back. The rush of demons stopped as if frozen in place. "Back, back to your camps, idiots!" the voice continued, as someone began to move through the crowd. "They're with me."<br />
<br />
The crowd of mobs parted, and out came a teir'dal with jet black hair and a big smile. He was carrying a clipboard and quill.<br />
<br />
"Well, I'll be damned!" the dark elf said. "Why the hells didn't you write you were coming?"<br />
<br />
"Nice timing, Vven." Verdad replied.<br />
<br />
"It's all about the timing." Vven agreed, looking from Verdad to Cami. "Cami, looking wonderful, amazing what a month asleep in Hate can do for the skin...."<br />
<br />
"Thank you, Vven." Camille said, smiling despite herself.<br />
<br />
"And is that Talvarien? With ARMS?" Vven exclaimed. "I almost didn't recognize you!"<br />
<br />
"Hi Vven." Talvarien said, wincing at the recollection of having his arms ripped off in the Plane of Nightmare.<br />
<br />
"And Rocsalt, Grelin...." Vven nodded. "What, is Razor's Edge coming up for a raid? We're not open yet..."<br />
<br />
"Razor disbanded after River died, Vven..." Camille said quietly.<br />
<br />
"Ah, I had heard River slipped in Velks." Vven said carefully. "I would have come to the funeral, but I didn't think dancing on his grave would be appropriate..."<br />
<br />
"You wouldn't have danced on his grave." Camille said, not believing the teir'dal for a minute.<br />
<br />
"Well, maybe just a LITTLE dance...." Vven laughed. "Boy was Inny upset when River didn't end up here..."<br />
<br />
"You look well, Vven." Camille said, changing subjects.<br />
<br />
"Hate has been good for inky." Vven agreed. "I found my true calling, as an administrator here. So what do you think of the place? All my idea..." He turned and gestured broadly to the buildings behind him with the clipboard. "Hate 2.0!"<br />
<br />
"Interesting..." Roc commented, face not registering if he cared for the changes or not.<br />
<br />
"Vven, I came up here to talk to you about something...." Camille began.<br />
<br />
"Sure sure..." Vven said, taking her by the hand and pulling her away from the well. "Let's talk in the lounge. I can give you the nickel tour as we head over."<br />
<br />
"Hate has a lounge?" Rocsalt asked, nose wrinkling.<br />
<br />
"Oh, Hate has a lot of new things." Vven said, looking at him sidelong slyly.<br />
<br />
And, as the others following the teir'dal and Camille, they made their way south into the streets of Hate.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
