<!-- spacer --></td><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td></tr></table>
<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post147334"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"This first part of Hate is the same 'ole, same 'ole." Vven said, pointing to various buildings with the quill. "Just with better scenery. You like it? Sorta like Katta without the fog machine." <br />
<br />
Various mobs were working their way in and out of the buildings, dragging in furniture, removing large sacks of trash, typical construction site. They paused for a moment as a spite golem crossed their path, pushing a large harpsichord into a nearby building. <br />
<br />
"ANOTHER piano?" Vven asked the spite golem incredulously. <br />
<br />
"Sorry, Boss." the spite said apologetically. "Maestro's orders."<br />
<br />
"Soooo old school." Vven sighed, steering them around the musical instrument. Then in a low whisper he added, "Maestro has been pitching a fit ever since I took over operations in southern Hate. So since he was assigned Zone In, every other building has a freakin' piano. Ridiculous waste of money. What are we going to do, play classical music and BORE them to death?"<br />
<br />
Camille just shrugged, not knowing quite what to say.<br />
<br />
"Ok, so, here's Northern Hate, clerics here, spites there, yadda yadda..." Vven said dismissively. "Now, we're getting near my area. Cami, do you remember way back when, why Innoruuk didn't want to keep River in Hate?"<br />
<br />
The answer was on her lips in a second. She still remembered the day she woke up from her long sleep in End Game like it was yesterday. "He said because River would turn Hate into an amusement park." she recalled.<br />
<br />
"Right!" Vven exclaimed, moving them along. "So after you two left, I started thinking, Hmm, not a bad idea. Took me half a year driving Inny crazy but..." He turned the corner and made a grand gesture. "Voila!"<br />
<br />
They stopped dead in their tracks and gaped.<br />
<br />
There, sprawled out before them, lights flashing, was a huge demonic....carnival. Booths lined the streets, with dozens of games. A rollercoaster roared in the distance. Ramps leading to different attractions were everywhere, complete with rulers protruding from the ground with height requirements for certain rides.<br />
<br />
"Oh...my...gods..." Roc blinked in disgust, and started coughing.<br />
<br />
"You like it??" Vven asked happily, clapping his hands together. Fortunately, Roc at the moment could not respond.<br />
<br />
An abhorrant, stone wings flapping, flew up to Vven carrying a large box. "The advertisments are in, Boss!" the abhorrant exclaimed.<br />
<br />
Vven excused himself for a moment while they stared at the glitzy travesty before them and took one of the fliers out of the box. As he skimmed it, his face grew dark.<br />
<br />
"What the hells is this? 'Come to 'isnnyland!'....'ISNNYLAND?" he barked. He rolled up the flier and rapped the abhorrant over the head with it. "Idiot, do you even proofread this crap before you send it out? It's INNY'S LAND, not 'isnnyland, you moron! Get this back to the printers before they close!"<br />
<br />
"Yes Boss." the abhorrant said miserably, lugging the box back the way he came.<br />
<br />
"Can't find good help nowadays." Vven sighed, looking at them apologetically. "Anyway, come, I'll show you some of the highlights!"<br />
<br />
They followed him mutely, too amazed to say anything.<br />
<br />
"The whole thing, you know, came to me in a flash. I mean, when I was adventuring with the rest of you saps down on Norrath, I used to think 'and THIS is what I get? Camp the Arch Mage in Guk for 8 hours for these crappy PANTS?'...risk vs. reward was more imbalanced than casters vs. melee in the Arena. Why bother? So, I figure, after you battle it out in Maestro's area, read:RISK, then you get to inky's area, read:REWARD."<br />
<br />
"Oh my gods, I LOVE this!" Talvarien exclaimed. Rocsalt just stared at him.<br />
<br />
"Ok ok ok," Vven said, speaking at a fast clip. "Over there you got the Pirates of Guntrak, over here you have Tolapmuj's Wild Ride, and heh here's a little game I had dedicated to Whizbang, that little punk." He steered them towards a booth with a board on it, with about half a dozen holes cut into it. Chained to the board on a long cord was a fist sized replica of Pedi, Whizbang's wife. A large sign over the booth indicated the name of the game: Whack-A-Gnome.<br />
<br />
"Hehh," Verdad said. "I like this one."<br />
<br />
"Guarunteed to be a hit!" Vven exclaimed proudly. "Pop in a plat, and a little Whizbang pops out of anyone of these holes for a few seconds. The more Whizbangs you bonk with the Pedi Hammer here, the more tickets you get, till you win an Inny Doll! Whiz even goes 'Damnation!' when you hit him. Priceless!"<br />
<br />
"Can I play now?" Verdad asked hopefully.<br />
<br />
"Later!" Vven said, pulling Cami and the rest deeper into the carnival. "I want to show you my biggest brainchild!"<br />
<br />
They paused as a new sign loomed. In large pink letters, they read 'END GAME GROVE'.<br />
<br />
"...'End Game Grove' ..???" Camille exclaimed.<br />
<br />
"Hey!" Vven replied. "I had some of my best laughs during End Game! So I dedicated a whole section of the park to it. Come, look!"<br />
<br />
They walked under the sign, Camille still shaking her head, after Vven.<br />
<br />
In one section they found a rather large booth. On the counter, was mock pieces of a human being. Inside the booth sat a sad looking squid, dressed rather pathetically in a dragon costume. An ire ghast in a carnival barker's hat was sitting on a stool outside it. The sign over the booth read 'STARVE WUOSHI'.<br />
<br />
"Starve Wuoshi!" Talvarien replied in delight.<br />
<br />
"That's right kid, Starve Wuoshi!" the ire ghast piped up, sensing a customer. "Just 5 plat to try your luck! The object is to pick up these pieces of human meat and toss them past old Wuoshi there! If you can get three body parts past her without her catching and eating them, you can get this genuine imitation Shattered Emerald of Corruption, just like all the rangers want!"<br />
<br />
"Imitation?" Talvarien asked, smile fading. "Doesn't the real Shattered Emerald of Corruption drop in Hate?"<br />
<br />
"Hheh, yeah kid," the ghast chuckled, rolling his eyes. "Surrre it does."<br />
<br />
"Hard as hells to win too!" Vven added. "See our Wuoshi there? Out of work squid-thing from the Plane of Water. Not much to look at, but the damned things got sixteen arms! Nothing gets past him!"<br />
<br />
Camille took a good look at the pieces of 'human' on the counter. Her eyes came to rest on the head. Something about it was familiar. Long black hair, moustache....<br />
<br />
"Vven!" she shrieked.<br />
<br />
"What??" he asked, recoiling from the anger in her voice.<br />
<br />
"You are feeding this Wuoshi thing a dummy of RIVER?" she yelled.<br />
<br />
"Ok ok ok! Poor taste!" Vven said as she bonked him. "I'll have it changed to Verdad or something!"<br />
<br />
"You better..." Camille warned.<br />
<br />
"Take a picture with Ramluk?" Vven said, trying to lead them away from the replica of Riverdane's dismembered body. A large spite golem in ogre battle armor stood looking bored against a pole.<br />
<br />
"Ogre." it said half-heartedly.<br />
<br />
"That's OGGA!," Vven whispered fiercely, jabbing the thing in its side. "You're making me look bad!"<br />
<br />
"Ogga." it said, shrugging its massive shoulders.<br />
<br />
"Ok ok ok." Vven said, eyes murderous, pulling them in yet another direction. "This one's my favorite. Check this out!" He dragged them to a large mechanical model, rather realistically rendered of a large tree, with the features of a beautiful elven woman etched into the bark. Above it, was a pretty sign that said 'The Tunare Tree'.<br />
<br />
"Ok, stand back!" he said, as a forsaken revenant ran up to him with a bottle of liquor and a torch. Vven took both and stood in front of the tree.<br />
<br />
"Ok, I learned this trick from an old friend Momur....that chick makes me look like an amateur." And with that he took a huge swig of alcohol, holding it in his mouth. Then he quickly brought the torch near his face, and with a woooosh spit out the drink into the fire. A huge flame shot from his mouth, hitting the tree and enveloping it in fire.<br />
<br />
Immediately, two eyes in the tree opened up as it started to burn. The woman's mouth started opening and closing as the branches began flailing about. "Oh no!" she wailed. "It's End Game! I'm burning! I'm burninggg!"<br />
<br />
Vven wiped his mouth and stood back proudly. "Gods I love that."<br />
<br />
Camille addressed the demented dark elf from a distance. "Vven, this is...fascinating. But we really need to talk."<br />
<br />
"Ok ok ok." Vven said, steering them away from the tree, which was still moaning something about 'The tear! The tear!'. "Let's hit the bar."<br />
<br />
"A bar in Hate." Rocsalt murmured.<br />
<br />
"Yeah!" Vven said, stopping in front of a large building. "Here it is." A large sign above named the bar. It said: JEERS.<br />
<br />
Vven pushed his way in. The place was packed with undead, drinking and having a rather good time. When he entered, they all lifted their mugs of beer as one. "Vven!" they chorused.<br />
<br />
"Hey." he waved, then turned to his companions. "Where everybody knows your name." he said, motioning to a large unoccupied table to the side.<br />
<br />
Sitting down, Vven finally slowed down, and looked at Cami.<br />
<br />
"Ok, Cam. What do you want to talk about?" he asked.<br />
<br />
Cami took a deep breath, and said, "What do you know about Greig Veneficus?"<br />
<br />
Vven's blue skin drained almost of all color.<br />
<br />
"Oh boy. There's a name I try not to think about." he said, twitching nervously.<br />
<br />
"Tell me." Camille insisted.<br />
<br />
And he did.</font></p>
	
