<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post147829"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Wizard</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Vazaelle<br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"At the end of the steps, we're in this, bedroom or something. And it's occupied. By this...blob of purple snot, just...gross. It's got eyes and a mouth, and two arms, and its sorta floating there, and we're getting sick looking at it when it notices us."<br />
<br />
"Greig..." Camille murmured.<br />
<br />
"Yeah," Vven said, looking up from his empty mug for a moment. "The thing opens its maw and growls 'After all this time, invaders in the home of Grieg Veneficus! Prepare to meet thy doom!' or some flowery crap like that. But Vinny, quick as a whip says 'You Greg?' and the thing says, 'I am Grieg.' and Vinny says, 'Well you can thank us later, man. We just killed a raid that was on their way to kill you.' Randolf goes to say something but I just kick him, and he howls and shuts up. Probably the smartest move he ever made. And this Grieg thing floats over to us and it's like staring and I can hear Moelle starting to murmur an evac. And then the thing smiles, freakin' SMILES, the ugliest smile you ever seen, and says 'Thank you.' I almost fell over. Thank you!<br />
<br />
So Vinny, being the gentleman he is, offers the bottle of Black to this thing, and the thing looks at it for a second, and then takes it in one drippy hand, takes it to his lips, and CHUGS it. Chugs Black Poison straight, like it was water. We're just staring at this thing, half glad he polished the bottle off cause no WAY I'm bringing that bottle to my lips after he wrapped his around it, when he goes two shades darker purple and pukes all over the floor. Randolf the idiot starts laughing and someone kicks him, Moelle I think, and Grieg is sort of embarrassed and looking at Randolf like he wanted to kill him. And he's sorta wobbling now, and I'm thinking, this thing is as wasted as we are.<br />
<br />
So Vinny says, 'Why you in here all alone, man?' and the thing starts going off on Luclin trapped him there, and he wasn't strong enough in that form to get out, and how he hates her, and rambling on and on, cursing Luclin worse than some of the best teir'dal ranters I have heard. Then the thing starts, crying, and mixing in crying and cursing and we're all standing there looking at it feeling sorta disgusted. Then the thing looks up and says, 'You got through the traps, you can get me out of here!' and I'm thinking no friggin' way and say 'Yeah sure man, we'll get you out'. Vinny gives me this look but I just shrug but this thing is so happy Vinny just goes with it. 'Yeahyeah, no problem man.'. Well, the floating grape goes to leave down the stairs, but it's so wasted it crashes into the wall instead. "You're too gone to go now.' Vinny says, looking at it trying over and over to walk through the wall. 'Let's sober you up a little, sit down, play cards or something.'<br />
<br />
'Cards?' the blob says. And Vinny nods and pulls out his old deck of cards he had intended to use for strip poker with the girls before the idiot cousin showed up, and some dice. He motions for us to sit down, so we all do, near the blob thing in a circle.<br />
<br />
'Let's play Pain/Fear.' Vinny says. 'You know what that is?' Old Teir'dal card game, played with a deck and dice. Grieg just says 'No.' so Vinny starts telling him the rules, five players, each gets so many cards, you can only play a card off the top of your deck on the player to your left, and you have choices, Pain or Fear. The guy you play your card on has to play the card off the top of HIS deck against you, and you have the option of Pain, killing his card if its weaker than yours, or Fear, sending his card to the bottom of his deck if it is stronger than yours, which is hard. Both players roll the dice, add the total to the cards value, compare, and the high total wins the hand. Fun game. Something to do. Hells, we were still wasted ourselves, somehow playing Pain/Fear with a purple turd didn't seem too odd.<br />
<br />
Well, Grieg gets this shifty look in his eyes, and goes behind the bed and pulls out this glowing rock. He comes back and sits down and drops the rock in the middle of us. 'There.' he goes, 'Now that will stop anyone using magic from cheating.'<br />
<br />
'What's that?' I ask, and he smiles all sly like.<br />
<br />
'Something I created.' he said looking all nasty. 'It puts up a radius that cancels all magic, in case one of you tries to alter what the cards look like.'<br />
<br />
Bah, paranoid bastard. Plus, it was exactly what I DID intend to do, so he sort of crimped my game style.<br />
<br />
Vinny starts dealing out the cards to Grieg, me, Dooma and Moe. Then Randolf is standing there, and goes 'hey I wanna play.' Like the idiot knows how to play Pain/Fear. Plus, it was a five person game, no room. We just laughed and called him names. We didn't let poor Randolf play in any Pain/Fear games. Vinny told him to watch and learn and Randolf grumbles and stands there, sorta drooling watching.<br />
<br />
'I hate kids.' Greig said, staring weird like at Randolf. Vinny's dealing, making small talk, saying 'Yeah me too, always playing on my damned lawn.' which starts Moe off laughing like a nut, cause there are no lawns in Neriak. <br />
<br />
'Are there many children like this one out there still?' Greig asks.<br />
<br />
'Kids?' Vinny says, dealing. 'No kids man, most of the children up here went back to Norrath after we figured out how to get back to the moon.'<br />
<br />
'The way back was discovered?' Grieg says, all shocked like.<br />
<br />
'Yeah man a while ago, how long you been IN here?' Vinny says, still dealing out the cards. But Grieg just starts mumbling crazy like again, and then says 'The children laughed and threw garbage at me, when they forced me in here. I hate them.'<br />
<br />
'You gunna jabber or play cards?' Vinny said. And Grieg mumbles something else, and then turns over his card. It's a ten. Vinny is sitting to his left, so turns over HIS card, and its a 7. So Vinny asks him if he wants to Pain or Fear. Grieg says Pain, figuring his card is already higher, that he'll be able to get rid of Vinny's 7 no problem. They both roll, and Grieg roll a 1 and Vinny gets a 6. That's Vinny, luck of the halflings. So they total at Grieg with an 11 and Vinny with a 13, and Vinny shakes his head sadly and tells Grieg to bury his card. Greig is sorta pissed but goes to do it.<br />
<br />
When SUDDENLY, Randolf starts braying like a damned donkey and pointing at Grieg and laughing, going 'He can't play Pain/Fear! He sucks!' an all sorts of stupid crap. And Grieg's face is getting more and more purple, and I want to kick Randolf but I'm sitting so he just goes on and on.<br />
<br />
Well, Grieg floats up and looks at Randolf, and he's mad. 'What am I, here for your amusement?' he yells, but Randolf can't stop laughing. 'What am I a clown to you? I'm here to make you laugh?' He's angry as hells, but Randolf isn't getting it, and the rest of us get real quiet, not knowing what to do. And Grieg is fuming, 'You think this is funny, you stupid moron?' Grieg is going, and Randolf must finally figure it out, cause he stops giggling and starts staring at Grieg, who's circling him at this moment. And something must have frightened him, cause suddenly, his pants get this growing stain in the front, and he just lets go where he's standing, pissing himself. And Grieg looks at the stain and smiles, and then all the anger goes out of his voice. 'Yeah, that was sorta funny, me losing like that, huh?' he says all nice like, and starts to laugh. Well, we're all on edge, and Randolf starts to giggle with him, thinking its ok. And then Grieg laughs some more, and damned if it wasn't infectious, all of us start laughing, I mean tears from your eyes laughing, Grieg laughing the loudest of all, Randolf right along with him.<br />
<br />
And then suddenly Grieg stops laughing and grabs Randolfby the arm and opening that big weird mouth of his, takes a bite out of the kid's neck. <br />
<br />
Blood gushes everywhere and w're just sitting there in shock and Randolf is making these gurgling noises and Grieg is just biting away, at the kid's face, arms, taking out huge chunks. We're all getting drenched as randolf's getting eaten and before long he's nothing but a piles of bloody flesh and we're all in a daze and Moelle is staring real hard at the glowing rock thinking the same thing I'm thinking....no evac with that thing cancelling magic.<br />
<br />
'Let's play cards.' Grieg says suddenly, as if nothing happened, and floats down again.<br />
<br />
'Um, sure.' Vinny says, trying to be cool, but his hands are shaking. It's not every day you see someone get eaten, you know?<br />
<br />
'Hate kids.' Grieg said again. 'I'd kill them all if I could.' <br />
<br />
'That's cool, man.' Vinny says, playing a card on Dooma, who's not even watching, she's just looking at her dead cousin.<br />
<br />
'I could you know,' Grieg rambles, 'When I get out of here I'm going to talk to a few creatures I know, and kill all the kids. On Norrath, they are now?'<br />
<br />
'Yeah yeah.' Vinny says, trying to tune him out. 'Dooma, you going to play or what?' but Dooma's still staring at the bloody cousin.<br />
<br />
'How you going to kill them?' Moelle asks timidly. I haven't ever heard Moe timid, but we were all a little rattled.<br />
<br />
'Drown them.' Grieg said.<br />
<br />
'That's going to take some time.' I said, poking Dooma in the side so we could get the game done and find some way out of there. Dooma came out of her stare and made a bad play and Vinny took her card, but I don't think he cared if he won or lost at that point.<br />
<br />
'I'll get them all in one shot.' Grieg nodded. 'Shift the moon off its orbit, mass flooding on Norrath, earthquakes, the works... lock up the portals to Luclin...let them all drown..."<br />
<br />
'How you going to move the moon?' I asked, intrigued despite the situation.<br />
<br />
'Rockets...' he whispered. 'With some help...'<br />
<br />
Well at the time, this was before the gnomes and all started talking about rockets and jet packs and stuff, so I didn't know what the hells he was talking about.<br />
<br />
'Cool.' I said, playing a card on Moelle. But Moelle, eyes wide listening to Grieg, had a brainstorm, thank Inny.<br />
<br />
She stood up. 'Me and Dooma have to powder our noses. Excuse us.' And she grabbed Dooma by the hand and practically dragged her up the stairs out of the room. Me and Vinny caught the idea.<br />
<br />
'Um, yeah...' Vinny said, 'I have to go drain the weasel, I'll be right back.' and up he goes after the girls, leaving me alone with the Purple Blob from Outer Space. <br />
<br />
Grieg's not paying much attention, instead, reaching for the other bottle of Black Poison and starts drinking it.<br />
<br />
'I'm gunna smoke, if you don't mind.' I said, and then made a show of patting my pockets. 'Damned, Vinny has my smokes, I'll be right back.' Grieg just nods and keeps drinking, and I get up and hurry out after them. Then minute i get out the door, Moelle starts chanting and we port the hell out.<br />
<br />
I have never been so damned happy to be out of somewhere. Dooma is freaking out, saying 'How I am I going to tell Uncle Dvinn his son is dead??' and I'm like 'Ambassador Dvinn is your uncle??!' and you think you know a chick and all...<br />
<br />
Well Vinny suggests we just STFU and pretend like Randolf never came out with us. And after a while, Dooma sees this is a good idea and we agree to never mention this again. And that was the end of our relationship with THOSE two chicks.<br />
<br />
But me and Vinny, well we never said a thing to nobody after that. Until, now that is."<br />
<br />
And that being said, without asking Vven reached out for Grelin's untouched ale, and began drinking it down, the ghosts of his past fading from his eyes with each gulp.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><a href="report.php?s=3288aedf0a1cf8f86d293cf642ed2fa4&postid=147829">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=3288aedf0a1cf8f86d293cf642ed2fa4&action=getip&postid=147829">Logged</a></font></p>
	</td>
